'Di-mairt,' Tuesday, Mar's day, is a lucky day to begin cutting corn, or
doing any work requiring a sharp instrument. 'Mart gu gearradh,' Tuesday
for cutting. In Uist marriages always take place on Tuesday or Thursday.

'Di-ciadaoin,' Wednesday, the day of the first fast, from 'ciad,' first,
and 'aoin,' fast--Friday being the second and principal fast. Wednesday
was considered a lucky day.

